html(lang="")
    head
        // Tailwind CSS
        link(rel="stylesheet" href="app.pcss")

        // App CSS
        link(rel="stylesheet" href="app.css")

        title Young People Survey

    body
        div.container.mx-auto
            main
                aside
                    section#sectionIntro
                        h1.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 What does young generation things?
                        p.text-base By #[a(href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/sunitdeshpande/" target="_blank").text-blue-500.underline Sunit Deshpande]
                        br
                        p.text-base In 2013, students of the Statistics class at #[a(href="https://fses.uniba.sk/en/" target="_blank").text-blue-500.underline FSEV UK] were asked to invite their friends to participate in a survey. Data consists of responses to different questions by almost #[b 1010] different participant.  The original data source can be viewed at the following #[a(href="https://www.kaggle.com/miroslavsabo/young-people-survey" target="_blank").text-blue-500.underline link].
                        br
                        p.text-base The purpose of this visualization is to show different trends and patter than emerge in the responses given by the young participants. Please scroll down to view the visualization.
                    section#sectionAge
                        h1.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 Age Distribution
                        p Following bar chart shows the distribution of age for the participants involved in the survey. As seen from the graph the participants were people from the age of 15 to 30, with a mean of 20.61 and mode of 19.
                    section#sectionGender
                        h1.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 Gender
                        p Participants were from a more diverse group as shown by the doughnut chart to the left. Total of the participant for whom the response was collected, 41.3% were male and 58.7% were female.
                    section#sectionInterest
                        h1.text-xl.font-semibold.mb-2 Liking for a subject
                        p The given chart shows the liking for each subject based on gender. For each bubble chart, the size indicates the number of participants, the colour indicates the gender and the intensity of the colour indicate the level of interest for the given subject. You can also use the filters below to filter through the data.
                        h2.text-l.font-semibold.my-2.underline Filters
                        div.flex.flex-wrap.-mx-3.mb-2
                            div(class="w-full md:w-1/2 px-3 mb-6 md:mb-0")
                                label.block.uppercase.tracking-wide.text-gray-700.text-xs.font-bold.mb-2 Gender
                                div.relative
                                    select(class="block appearance-none w-full bg-gray-200 border border-gray-200 text-gray-700 py-3 px-4 pr-8 rounded leading-tight focus:outline-none focus:bg-white focus:border-gray-500")
                                        option All
                                        option Male
                                        option Female
                            div(class="w-full md:w-1/2 px-3 mb-6 md:mb-0")
                                label.block.uppercase.tracking-wide.text-gray-700.text-xs.font-bold.mb-2 Liking
                                div.relative
                                    select(class="block appearance-none w-full bg-gray-200 border border-gray-200 text-gray-700 py-3 px-4 pr-8 rounded leading-tight focus:outline-none focus:bg-white focus:border-gray-500")
                                        option All
                                        option Male
                                        option Female
                        h2.text-l.font-semibold.my-2.underline Legend
                        svg#sectionInterestLegend(width=300 height=400)

